<div id="prodAccordion">
  <div id="ProductDescription" class="Block Panel">
    <h3 class="sub-title1" style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
      [TAL2111] Technical Applications Liaison
    </h3>
    <div class="ProductDescriptionContainer prodAccordionContent">
      <p>
        <span class="careers-page-text-content"
          >Master’s or PhD level Biologist with motivation and a passion for
          chromatin biology/epigenetics to grow the sales of EpiCypher’s highly
          innovative technologies and services.</span
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        Founded in 2012, <strong>EpiCypher<sup>®</sup></strong> was created in
        response to the growing demand for high-quality reagents and services to
        study chromatin regulation and enable epigenetics-focused drug
        development. Our designer nucleosomes (dNucs) with fully defined histone
        post-translational modifications or DNA modifications power the
        <em>dCypher<sup>®</sup></em>
        Discovery Platform for dissecting epigenetic regulators in their
        physiological context, and the SNAP™ portfolio of Spike-in Controls for
        quantitative genome-scale studies. EpiCypher is at the cutting edge of
        chromatin mapping with the recent launch of the CUTANA™ platform for
        ultra-sensitive CUT&RUN and CUT&Tag assays. These provide major
        advantages over <em>ChIP-seq</em>, delivering high quality epigenomic
        data at a cost and ease-of-use accessible to a broad range of
        researchers.
      </p>

